==Latin==
===Etymology===
# '''[[Anno]]''' is the [[ablative]] of '''[[annus]]''' (''[[year]])''
# '''[[Domini]]''' is the [[genitive]] of '''[[Dominus]]''' (''the [[Lord]]'')

===Expression===
'''Anno Domini'''

# Latin terminology meaning "''in the year of our Lord Jesus Christ''". Years labeled ''AD'' represent year after the birth of Jesus. Years prior to Jesus' birth are labeled as ''BC'' (meaning ''before Christ'').

==== Translations ====
*Czech: [[léta Páně]] ''or'' [[roku Páně]] (''abbr.'' l.P., r.P., A.D.)
*{{msg:fi}}: [[Herran vuonna]]
*Russian: [[после]] [[рождество|Рождества]] [[Христов|Христова]] (pósle Roždestvá Xristóva) (''abbr.'' [[после Р. Хр.]])
*Slovak: [[rok#Slovak|roku Pána]] ''or'' [[Anno Domini#Latin|Anno Domini]] (''abbr.'' r.P., A.D.)

